records.addlTxt: Justice Point Pretrial Services DISCHARGE  Report received and filed.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE BENCH  WARRANT.

Attorney Corey R. Flynn in court.  Adam Joseph Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
 HEARING HELD VIA ZOOM/ LIVE STREAMING THROUGH DACAST.  Case in court for a calendar call. 
DEFENDANT FAILED TO APPEAR. Defense counsel advises the court he has been unsuccessful in contacting client.  State moves the court to lift the stay, issue a bench warrant, and forfeit the bail.
Court ordered bench warrant issued. Remand to Commissioner and no action on bail.

Defendant Jewel Teeria Gohangon not in court.  Adam Joseph Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD.
Matter scheduled for Status Conference.  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until the next court date.  Calendar call scheduled for May 6, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

Case scalendared in Branch 19  in error. Court ordered matter transferred to Correct Court Official Branch 30 due to the lower pending matter. Status Conference scheduled April 27, 2022 at 10:30am.
Defense counsel notified via email.

Defendant Jewel Teeria Gohangon in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Erika Strebel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
HEARING HELD VIA ZOOM/ LIVE STREAMING THROUGH DACAST. Case in court for a Pretrial Conference.
Defense in receipt of discovery and offer and request time to review and discuss with the defendant. 
Court ordered matter adjourned back to Branch 19 This hearing will be be held streamed Live through dacast- via Zoom.  Status conference scheduled for April 27, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.
Pre-trial conference on March 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court orders defendant TO JUSTICE POINT for supervision. Defendant to report to JUSTICE POINT LEVEL 4 immediately upon leaving court.  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY to be monitored by portable breathalyzers. 
IF THE DEFENDANT FAILS TO REPORT A WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.
The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in a manner and fashion as prescribed.
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
No driving without a valid license.

Defendant Jewel Teeria Gohangon in court.  Gerald Henry Alder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Ashley, Branch 19.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 19  for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant is Out-of-Custody. Court appearance in Out-Of-Custody Court, Room 221 Safety Building on 3/7/22 @ 1p
